1
00:00:08,096 --> 00:00:09,446
<i>My name is Melinda Gordon.</i>

2
00:00:12,243 --> 00:00:13,243
<i>I just got married,</i>

3
00:00:13,417 --> 00:00:14,817
<i>just moved to a small town,</i>

4
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:16,560
<i>just opened up an antique shop.</i>

5
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:18,420
<i>I might be just like you.</i>

6
00:00:19,967 --> 00:00:21,870
<i>Except from the time that I was a little girl,</i>

7
00:00:21,871 --> 00:00:23,771
<i>I knew that I could talk to the dead.</i>

8
00:00:25,071 --> 00:00:26,221
<i>It's all right, honey.</i>

9
00:00:26,319 --> 00:00:28,719
<i>Earthbound spirits, my grandmother called them,</i>

10
00:00:28,817 --> 00:00:32,370
<i>the ones who have not crossed over because they have unfinished business with the living,</i>

11
00:00:32,372 --> 00:00:33,875
<i>and they come to me for help.</i>

12
00:00:35,304 --> 00:00:36,406
<i>To tell you my story,</i>

13
00:00:36,968 --> 00:00:38,316
<i>I have to tell you theirs.</i>

14
00:01:08,176 --> 00:01:09,520
- So, will you do it?
- No.

15
00:01:10,267 --> 00:01:11,212
Not fair.

16
00:01:11,406 --> 00:01:14,223
You know, I have told you a thousand times I'm not telling your boss his dead,

17
00:01:14,226 --> 00:01:17,622
disgruntled employee put a hex on him. First of all, there's no such thing.

18
00:01:17,627 --> 00:01:18,723
He doesn't know that!

19
00:01:18,747 --> 00:01:21,082
You know, there are people waiting for you in the light-- go.

20
00:01:21,088 --> 00:01:22,430
You're not the boss of me.

21
00:01:22,528 --> 00:01:23,473
Real mature, Gary.

22
00:01:27,946 --> 00:01:29,192
Don't marry him, Elaine.

23
00:01:29,217 --> 00:01:31,612
He just wants our money. I know guys like this.

24
00:01:31,738 --> 00:01:32,681
Conrad.

25
00:01:37,708 --> 00:01:38,650
Good morning.

26
00:01:41,215 --> 00:01:42,943
- So, did you talk to her?
- Your wife?

27
00:01:42,947 --> 00:01:44,492
Yes, my wife at the rest home.

28
00:01:44,925 --> 00:01:47,890
I'm sorry, I've been really busy, but I will try to get out there this weekend.

29
00:01:47,898 --> 00:01:49,661
- I promise.
- Sure, don't worry about me.

30
00:01:49,665 --> 00:01:53,160
I've only been dead for 50 years. I've got all the time in the world!

31
00:01:53,846 --> 00:01:55,350
- Ah, good morning.
- Hey!

32
00:01:55,798 --> 00:01:57,391
- How you doing?
- Oh, you know.

33
00:01:57,595 --> 00:01:58,590
Same old, same old.

34
00:02:03,885 --> 00:02:05,983
You know, you seem suspiciously cheerful.

35
00:02:06,715 --> 00:02:08,151
Hmm, do I?

36
00:02:11,436 --> 00:02:12,380
Oh, well.

37
00:02:13,525 --> 00:02:15,121
I met somebody the other night.

38
00:02:15,437 --> 00:02:16,381
Do tell.

39
00:02:16,397 --> 00:02:19,241
Ok, he's a teacher at the high school, but at night he's

40
00:02:19,267 --> 00:02:22,460
this unbelievable spoken word poet. You have to hear his stuff.

41
00:02:22,698 --> 00:02:23,642
He's handsome.

42
00:02:23,985 --> 00:02:24,930
He's sensitive.

43
00:02:24,988 --> 00:02:26,301
- And he's tall.
- Sold!

44
00:02:27,338 --> 00:02:30,612
Actually he's performing tonight at this poetry slam thing in Bay Ridge.

45
00:02:30,626 --> 00:02:32,171
- Do you want to go?
- Absolutely.

46
00:02:32,177 --> 00:02:34,260
I want to meet the guy that has you looking like this.

47
00:02:34,267 --> 00:02:35,210
Like what?

48
00:02:35,225 --> 00:02:38,170
Like you just grabbed the gold ring on the merry-go-round.

49
00:02:45,938 --> 00:02:47,080
You know, like really.

50
00:02:48,387 --> 00:02:50,130
Um, so should we take my car to the reading?

51
00:02:50,135 --> 00:02:52,773
Uh, no, I should probably drive on my own. Otherwise I'll have to double back.

52
00:02:52,777 --> 00:02:54,573
Oh, ok. You have the directions, right?

53
00:02:54,575 --> 00:02:55,522
- Yes.
- Ok.

54
00:02:56,287 --> 00:02:57,231
Evening, ma'am.

55
00:02:58,415 --> 00:03:00,172
There's a chill in the air tonight.

56
00:03:00,175 --> 00:03:01,773
That's why I have on my jacket.

57
00:03:09,647 --> 00:03:10,993
I'm not even gonna ask.

58
00:03:11,526 --> 00:03:12,470
Yeah.

59
00:03:12,476 --> 00:03:13,421
- Ok.
- Ok.

60
00:03:14,938 --> 00:03:16,583
- See you there.
- See you there.

61
00:03:43,878 --> 00:03:44,820
You.

62
00:03:46,005 --> 00:03:47,550
You're the one who can see us.

63
00:03:48,658 --> 00:03:49,602
Do I know you?

64
00:03:50,645 --> 00:03:51,593
It was a cemetery.

65
00:03:54,018 --> 00:03:54,963
Melinda.

66
00:04:57,506 --> 00:05:01,500
