582
00:35:16,667 --> 00:35:18,610
There isn't anything I don't tell Jim.

583
00:35:19,038 --> 00:35:19,982
Ok.

584
00:35:23,666 --> 00:35:24,663
Is that really true

585
00:35:25,197 --> 00:35:26,691
that you tell Jim everything?

586
00:35:27,247 --> 00:35:28,190
Yeah, why?

587
00:35:28,568 --> 00:35:30,133
Mmm, I'm surprised, I guess.

588
00:35:31,335 --> 00:35:33,860
I never told your father about my visions.

589
00:35:34,518 --> 00:35:36,561
I was afraid it would be too disturbing.

590
00:35:36,958 --> 00:35:39,003
Course he ended up leaving me anyway, so

591
00:35:39,636 --> 00:35:42,980
- so much for my instincts on that one.
- You never talk about him.

592
00:35:44,405 --> 00:35:45,350
Why should I?

593
00:35:45,905 --> 00:35:47,000
He's out of our life.

594
00:35:49,307 --> 00:35:51,053
But I must say in retrospect,

595
00:35:51,546 --> 00:35:52,893
maybe if I had told him...

596
00:35:54,418 --> 00:35:56,912
Course it's water under the bridge now, isn't it.

597
00:35:57,526 --> 00:35:58,952
Time of death, 14:35.

598
00:36:09,226 --> 00:36:10,172
Mom,

599
00:36:10,588 --> 00:36:11,530
did you see that?

600
00:36:12,955 --> 00:36:13,902
What?

601
00:36:14,465 --> 00:36:15,411
No.

602
00:36:20,128 --> 00:36:21,071
Yes.

603
00:36:23,306 --> 00:36:24,773
Yes, I did.

604
00:36:34,976 --> 00:36:36,351
Andrea, I saw one.

605
00:36:36,915 --> 00:36:38,031
You did? Where?

606
00:36:38,256 --> 00:36:41,043
At the hospital. I never lost my gift. They've just gone away.

607
00:36:41,046 --> 00:36:42,542
But I don't get it. Where to?

608
00:36:42,576 --> 00:36:44,073
No idea. One thing at a time.

609
00:36:44,748 --> 00:36:47,342
Wow, this probably sounds like an odd conversation.

610
00:36:47,686 --> 00:36:48,632
No, no.

611
00:36:50,625 --> 00:36:51,572
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

612
00:36:51,687 --> 00:36:52,683
She'll explain it to you.

613
00:36:52,688 --> 00:36:55,711
Ashton, you wouldn't happen to have a copy of your poem with you, would you?

614
00:36:55,715 --> 00:36:57,820
My poem? No, it's all in my head.

615
00:36:58,755 --> 00:37:01,491
I'm trying to remember this part about who can resist the wind force.

616
00:37:01,495 --> 00:37:04,212
You said the tortured ghosts went immediately, and the young ones--

617
00:37:04,228 --> 00:37:07,200
The young and the passionate resist the best-- sometimes for days.

618
00:37:07,206 --> 00:37:10,901
Right, sometimes for days! Which means that I still have time. Thank you.

619
00:37:11,016 --> 00:37:12,660
Wait, wait! Where are you going?

620
00:37:13,567 --> 00:37:15,613
Brian's still out there. I'm sure of it.

621
00:37:15,756 --> 00:37:16,703
I just missed him.

622
00:37:22,478 --> 00:37:24,473
Ok, this is gonna take some explaining.

623
00:37:25,068 --> 00:37:26,012
Yeah.

624
00:37:30,347 --> 00:37:31,173
Melinda.

625
00:37:31,177 --> 00:37:32,170
I can help Caitlin.

626
00:37:32,487 --> 00:37:34,981
- I wasn't sure before.
- What are you doing here?

627
00:37:35,575 --> 00:37:38,172
I'm absolutely sure that Brian is still earthbound.

628
00:37:38,536 --> 00:37:40,882
What part of "leave me alone" is hard for you?

629
00:37:40,946 --> 00:37:44,181
The part where I have to abandon somebody that I know I can help.

630
00:37:44,188 --> 00:37:45,241
I'm sorry, I won't do it.

631
00:37:45,245 --> 00:37:46,141
Aunt Diane.

632
00:37:46,148 --> 00:37:48,392
Melinda, maybe this wasn't such a good idea.

633
00:37:48,415 --> 00:37:51,611
I mean, Caitlin has resisted, and you're going through your own loss of abilities.

634
00:37:51,615 --> 00:37:54,051
No, I won't lose faith in my gift anymore.

635
00:37:55,266 --> 00:37:58,311
I know I can help you find Brian, but you have to come with me right now.

636
00:37:58,315 --> 00:37:59,262
No!

637
00:37:59,126 --> 00:38:01,851
Just stop it, ok? I just need to be left alone.

638
00:38:02,697 --> 00:38:03,642
Caitlin...

639
00:38:05,006 --> 00:38:05,951
you listen to her.

640
00:38:07,055 --> 00:38:08,932
Aunt Diane told me what she can do.

641
00:38:09,707 --> 00:38:12,152
I don't know if i believe in all that stuff, but

642
00:38:12,486 --> 00:38:13,783
I think maybe you should.

643
00:38:14,226 --> 00:38:15,671
Dad, what are you talking about?

644
00:38:15,678 --> 00:38:17,171
Honey, I know you're in pain.

645
00:38:18,407 --> 00:38:20,200
I know I haven't been here for you,

646
00:38:20,717 --> 00:38:22,711
but I know this boy means a lot to you.

647
00:38:24,287 --> 00:38:25,431
I understand that now.

648
00:38:27,226 --> 00:38:28,570
And I don't want this pain

649
00:38:28,987 --> 00:38:30,921
eating you up inside, Caitlin.

650
00:38:31,327 --> 00:38:32,472
If you can find peace,

651
00:38:33,355 --> 00:38:34,753
that's what I want for you.

652
00:38:35,917 --> 00:38:37,611
Daddy, it hurts so bad.

653
00:38:39,186 --> 00:38:40,453
Oh, honey, honey, honey.

654
00:38:42,405 --> 00:38:43,353
I know.

655
00:38:44,676 --> 00:38:46,023
Oh, you're my little girl.

656
00:38:46,976 --> 00:38:48,223
You're everything to me.

657
00:38:49,805 --> 00:38:50,751
Thank you.

658
00:38:56,096 --> 00:38:58,540
I came here once before, but I gave up too soon.

659
00:38:58,737 --> 00:39:00,753
Something is pulling the spirits away, Caitlin,

660
00:39:00,758 --> 00:39:02,602
but the young and strong can resist.

661
00:39:03,765 --> 00:39:05,152
Brian is here. I know it.

662
00:39:06,097 --> 00:39:07,552
- I just know he is.
- Ok.

663
00:39:08,156 --> 00:39:09,102
Come on.

664
00:39:22,367 --> 00:39:23,312
My ring!

665
00:39:24,377 --> 00:39:25,322
It's here.

666
00:39:26,788 --> 00:39:27,783
Caitlin, he's here.

667
00:39:29,007 --> 00:39:29,952
Brian is?

668
00:39:30,378 --> 00:39:31,321
Right now?

669
00:39:32,116 --> 00:39:33,811
Your ring, it acted as an anchor.

670
00:39:34,256 --> 00:39:36,311
Sometimes ghosts can attach themselves to things

671
00:39:36,318 --> 00:39:39,162
that have a deeper meaning to them. It can give them strength.

672
00:39:39,167 --> 00:39:41,082
Something's been trying to pull me away.

673
00:39:41,086 --> 00:39:42,032
Something bad.

674
00:39:44,455 --> 00:39:47,203
Let's get out of here. That wind could start up again.

675
00:39:57,327 --> 00:39:59,640
Please tell her. I didn't want to break up with her.

676
00:39:59,648 --> 00:40:01,492
He didn't want to break up, Caitlin.

677
00:40:01,596 --> 00:40:02,542
He didn't?

678
00:40:04,106 --> 00:40:05,052
Who was that girl?

679
00:40:05,976 --> 00:40:07,870
The one I saw him with in the street.

680
00:40:09,175 --> 00:40:11,162
Caitlin, she was my dance teacher.

681
00:40:12,506 --> 00:40:13,522
Your dance teacher?

682
00:40:14,396 --> 00:40:15,342
His dance teacher?

683
00:40:17,845 --> 00:40:18,790
Oh, my god.

684
00:40:19,577 --> 00:40:21,723
He was learning how to dance just for me?

685
00:40:22,466 --> 00:40:23,861
I wanted to make you happy.

686
00:40:24,437 --> 00:40:27,602
I wanted to be able to dance with you and not look like an idiot.

687
00:40:27,606 --> 00:40:29,252
He was trying to make you happy.

688
00:40:29,998 --> 00:40:32,140
- He thought his dancing was--
- horrible.

689
00:40:33,525 --> 00:40:35,880
I just saw her, and she looked so pretty.

690
00:40:38,696 --> 00:40:41,290
And I was afraid that you woke up and realized that

691
00:40:41,637 --> 00:40:43,581
you shouldn't be with someone like me.

692
00:40:44,155 --> 00:40:48,502
Caitlin, I woke up every day and realized how lucky I was to be with someone like you.

693
00:40:49,157 --> 00:40:50,252
Didn't you know that?

694
00:40:50,605 --> 00:40:52,050
Didn't you know I loved you?

695
00:40:52,308 --> 00:40:54,653
He wants you to know that he woke up every day

696
00:40:55,316 --> 00:40:57,260
thinking how lucky he was to have you.

697
00:40:58,748 --> 00:41:01,341
He wants to know if you knew how much he loved you.

698
00:41:01,416 --> 00:41:02,361
I know now.

699
00:41:04,907 --> 00:41:05,852
Brian,

700
00:41:06,038 --> 00:41:08,282
I don't know how I'm gonna live without you.

701
00:41:09,065 --> 00:41:12,610
You're the only person that I've ever met that's made me feel special.

702
00:41:13,915 --> 00:41:14,862
Like I count.

703
00:41:17,647 --> 00:41:19,292
Tell her she'll find that again.

704
00:41:21,057 --> 00:41:22,502
Tell her that I want her to.

705
00:41:23,907 --> 00:41:24,851
For me.

706
00:41:24,978 --> 00:41:27,023
He believes that you'll find that again,

707
00:41:27,528 --> 00:41:28,971
and he wants you to for him.

708
00:41:29,357 --> 00:41:31,453
I will never find anyone like you, Brian.

709
00:41:32,367 --> 00:41:33,610
You learned how to dance

710
00:41:34,476 --> 00:41:35,423
just for me!

711
00:41:39,478 --> 00:41:41,320
And now we'll never get that chance.

712
00:41:49,035 --> 00:41:50,330
Caitlin, close your eyes.

713
00:41:50,627 --> 00:41:52,173
- What?
- Just close your eyes.

714
00:41:53,936 --> 00:41:54,882
Brian...

715
00:41:55,837 --> 00:41:57,882
I want you to take Caitlin in your arms.

716
00:41:58,807 --> 00:41:59,753
For real?

717
00:42:00,007 --> 00:42:00,951
For real.

718
00:42:01,678 --> 00:42:05,441
It may take her a minute to feel it, but I want you to show her what you learned.

719
00:42:05,448 --> 00:42:08,640
And you have to be open to this, Caitlin, ok? Just trust Brian.

720
00:42:09,536 --> 00:42:10,482
I do.

721
00:42:12,478 --> 00:42:13,423
Ok, Brian.

722
00:42:19,546 --> 00:42:20,492
I feel him.

723
00:42:23,498 --> 00:42:25,441
It's called a box step. Pretty simple.

724
00:42:26,948 --> 00:42:27,893
It's the box step.

725
00:43:19,655 --> 00:43:20,953
And then he crossed over?

726
00:43:21,028 --> 00:43:22,122
Then he crossed over.

727
00:43:23,637 --> 00:43:24,582
That's beautiful.

728
00:43:24,625 --> 00:43:26,170
Yeah, it was something to see.

729
00:43:26,595 --> 00:43:27,541
The power of love.

730
00:43:28,637 --> 00:43:29,630
Strong stuff, love.

731
00:43:31,447 --> 00:43:32,321
Something

732
00:43:32,325 --> 00:43:33,673
I know a little bit about.

733
00:43:34,747 --> 00:43:37,292
Hey, what about your regulars? They come back yet?

734
00:43:37,778 --> 00:43:39,470
- Where is Homer?
- Still missing.

735
00:43:39,966 --> 00:43:40,913
All of them.

736
00:43:41,348 --> 00:43:44,743
But at least we know I didn't lose my gift. I saw two ghosts today.

737
00:43:45,255 --> 00:43:47,362
Look at how she sparkles when she says that.

738
00:43:47,368 --> 00:43:50,012
Yeah, I'll admit it. I enjoy being back in the game.

739
00:43:54,115 --> 00:43:55,113
Although that wind,

740
00:43:56,637 --> 00:43:58,523
it was warm and so creepy.

741
00:44:01,508 --> 00:44:03,800
- What do you think it means?
- I wish I knew.





